<doc f='codebrowser/malloc/arena.c' l='210'>/* The following two functions are registered via thread_atfork() to
   make sure that the mutexes remain in a consistent state in the
   fork()ed version of a thread.  Also adapt the malloc and free hooks
   temporarily, because the `atfork&apos; handler mechanism may use
   malloc/free internally (e.g. in LinuxThreads). */</doc>
